text=(:nolinkwikiwords:)%0a!! CINNAMON CRUSTED PORK CHOPS WITH APPLES &amp; SAGE%0a%0aBy [[http://www.columbian.com:80/users/marypaleoinapinch/ | Mary Helmes]]%0a%0aJune 27, 2012%0a%0a[[#ingredients]]%0a!!Ingredients%0a* 3 Apples%0a* 3 Shallots%0a* 5 tablespoon Coconut Oil%0a* 2 tablespoon Chopped Fresh Sage%0a* Cinnamon%0a* Salt%0a* 5 Large Bone-In Pork Chops%0a* &frac14; cup White Wine (I like gewurtz with pork)%0a%0a[[#directions]]%0a!!Directions%0a%0a# Slice Apples.%0a# Thinly slice Shallots.%0a# Chop Sage.%0a# Melt 4 TBSP of Coconut Oil in a large fry pan over Medium heat. Add Apples, Shallots and Sage. Saut&eacute; for 5 min. Remove Apple Saut&eacute; from pan and set aside.%0a# Show your Chops some love, rub a generous amount of Cinnamon &amp; Salt onto both sides.%0a# Melt the remanding 1 TBSP Coconut Oil in the fry pan.%0a# Place your Chops in fry pan.%0a# Sear on both sides for 2 minutes.%0a# Measure out &frac14; White Wine.%0a# Pour White Wine over Chops. Allow sauce to come to a boil &ndash; this will cook all the alcohol out.%0a# Add the Apple Saut&eacute; back to the fry pan, over the Pork Chops.%0a# Cover, turn heat down to Low. Let cook for 7 minutes (give or take, depending on thickness of meat).%0a%0a>>comment%3c%3c%0aSummary: Pork chops with applesauce has been a staple in many cultures; cooking pork with apples and onions/shallots is a divine way to prepare this meat. This recipe makes things go even better with the addition of cinnamon and sage.%0aTags: pork chops, apples, shallots, cinnamon, paleo%0a(:tags-hide pork chops, apples, shallots, cinnamon, paleo:)%0a(:title "CINNAMON CRUSTED PORK CHOPS WITH APPLES &amp; SAGE" by Paleo in a Pinch  | The Columbian:)%0aSource: http://www.columbian.com/weblogs/paleo-in-a-pinch/2012/jun/27/cinnamon-crusted-porkchops-with-apples-sage/%0aParent: (Recipes.)MainDishes%0aincludeme:[[Recipes.MainDishes]]%0aCategories:[[!Recipes]],[[!MainDish]],[[!AmericanCuisine]]%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0aPage saved at: Tue, 02 Oct 2012 23:44:07 -0500%0a%0a
